name: media_png_invalid_idat_crc_mismatch
description: |
  A deliberately invalid PNG whose image data is otherwise a valid 1x1 RGBA
  image, but the IDAT chunk CRC has one bit flipped. This catches decoders that
  trust compressed image data without verifying chunk integrity. The IHDR and
  IEND CRCs are correct, so the failure is isolated to IDAT integrity checking.

  This file is independently constructed for this corpus and is MIT licensed.
  The PNG specification defines the per-chunk CRC:
  https://www.w3.org/TR/png-3/#5CRC-algorithm
format: hex
decode-as: bytes
mime-type: image/png
licence: MIT
pair:
  - with: valid-minimal-rgba-1x1.input
    hint: tricky
tags:
  - "media"
  - "image"
  - "png"
  - "invalid-png"
  - "crc"
  - "idat"
  - "integrity"
---
89 50 4e 47 0d 0a 1a 0a
00 00 00 0d 49 48 44 52 00 00 00 01 00 00 00 01 08 06 00 00 00 1f 15 c4 89
00 00 00 0b 49 44 41 54 78 da 63 60 00 02 00 00 05 00 01 e9 fa dc d9
00 00 00 00 49 45 4e 44 ae 42 60 82
